de.iabg.mode
Interface ModeCorrelationUI

All Known Implementing Classes:
ModalAssuranceCriterionUI, OrthogonalityCheckUI
public interface ModeCorrelationUI

This interface declares basic functionality for the user interface of a JModeCorrelationPanel. This interface tries to follow the structure described in Swing for a Model-View-Controller. Generally, the JModeCorrelationPanel is instantiated and then a ModeCorelationUI is installed onto it. Any implementing classes of this interface must be able to add and remove their own layout, components, listeners, keyboard actions, and defaults. If the user interface is not completely uninstalled when called, it can lead to unpredictable results in the JModeCorrelationPanel.

Version:
September 12, 2008
Author:
Adam C. Dick, BSE
